The paper discusses the development of a physician advisory system that uses answer set programming and abductive reasoning to improve adherence to clinical practice guidelines for managing heart failure. This involves coding the guidelines and identifying missing symptoms and conditions that must be present for a treatment to be effective. This work involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational engineering (cs.CE), machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), and databases (cs.DB).
